00:46:16.679 --> 00:46:17.679
That's a big reason why we were able to move so quickly.

00:46:18.679 --> 00:46:22.679
But you're able to use Azure functions

00:46:23.679 --> 00:46:27.679
and again, any sort of third-party services as well.

00:46:27.679 --> 00:46:31.679
So if there is a service that your firm decides

00:46:32.679 --> 00:46:33.679
that is more beneficial to purchase

00:46:34.679 --> 00:46:35.679
and it's cheap enough,

00:46:36.679 --> 00:46:38.679
you can also integrate that into the same suite

00:46:39.679 --> 00:46:40.679
of microservices that you're doing

00:46:41.679 --> 00:46:43.679
and you save yourself the headache of developing it.

00:46:44.679 --> 00:46:46.679
So they don't have to be on the same compute node.

00:46:47.679 --> 00:46:50.679
They can be as spread out as it makes sense.

